    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><em>A slim and agile half-elf with medium-length wavy brown hair and alert green-gray eyes. Finnan wears simple light leather armor beneath a patched dark green cloak. A lute hangs at his side, a small dagger rests at his belt, and a plain amulet sits around his neck.</em></p><h3>Personality</h3><p>Warm, quick-witted, observant, theatrical, and quietly brave. Finnan uses humor and music to disarm suspicion, but becomes serious when the weak are threatened.</p><h3>Motivation</h3><p>To protect the forgotten children and poor families of the city while exposing corrupt officials from the shadows.</p><h3>Mannerisms</h3><p>Tunes his lute when nervous; smiles before delivering bad news; lowers his voice whenever children or orphanage matters are mentioned; scans exits while performing.</p><h3>Voice &amp; Accent</h3><p>Warm, melodic, playful, and slightly streetwise. Speaks like every sentence could become a song, but grows quiet and precise when danger is near.</p><h3>Bonds, Ideals, Flaws</h3><ul><li><strong>Bond:</strong> Finnan grew up in a city orphanage and still feels responsible for the children, caretakers, and street families who raised him.</li><li><strong>Ideal:</strong> Stories belong to everyone. Power should protect the vulnerable, not exploit them.</li><li><strong>Flaw:</strong> He trusts desperate people too easily and often takes personal risks before asking for help.</li></ul><hr><h3>GM Notes</h3><p>Use Finnan as a friendly urban contact, recurring quest giver, tavern performer, rumor source, or emotional anchor for city-based adventures. He works especially well when the party needs social leads rather than a combat solution.</p><h3>Secrets</h3><p>Finnan secretly belongs to a loose informant network that shares rumors to protect the vulnerable rather than profit from them.</p><h3>Relationships</h3><p>Old orphanage: emotional home and source of his strongest loyalty. Street performers: informal allies and rumor carriers. Poor families: people he protects with songs, favors, and warnings. Corrupt city official: suspected enemy tied to missing children.</p><h3>Plot Hooks</h3><p>1. A child from Finnan's old orphanage has vanished after being seen near a municipal archive.\n2. Finnan asks the party to quietly follow a corrupt city officer who visits the poor wards at night.\n3. A false rumor implicates Finnan in a theft, forcing the party to decide whether to protect him.\n4. Finnan's informant network uncovers signs of a noble-backed child labor or trafficking ring.</p><h3>Encounter Ideas</h3><p>1. Tavern performance interrupted by city guards.\n2. Chase through market alleys after a pickpocket carrying a coded note.\n3. Social investigation inside an orphanage threatened by eviction.\n4. Midnight meeting with informants beneath an old bridge.</p>",
